lead_paragraph: Kemba Walker scored 22 points, Troy Daniels made his first five 3-point attempts and finished with 17 points, and the Charlotte Hornets completed a four-game season sweep of the Brooklyn Nets with a 113-99 win on Friday night.

headline.print_headline: Walker, Daniels Lift Hornets to Season Sweep of Nets 113-99
